The paper deals with graph problems in the context of distributed computing, specifically in the MapReduce model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Data Structures and Algorithms, and Distributed Computing categories. The paper also discusses the computational power of the semi-MapReduce model and its equivalence to the congested clique model, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Congestion Control and Social Networks and Information categories.
